'''Wilguens Raphael Polynice Paugain''' (born 24 August 2001) is a Haitian professional football player who plays as [[right-back]] for [[S.V. Zulte Waregem|Zulte Waregem]]. A former youth international for France, he plays for the [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]].

==Career==
Paugain is a youth product of AS Nomexy Vincey and [[SAS Épinal|Épinal]], before moving to [[AS Nancy Lorraine|Nancy]]'s academy in 2015 where he finished his development. He debuted with their reserves in the [[Championnat National 3]] in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.estrepublicain.fr/sport/2019/11/23/photos-le-duel-entre-l-asnl-et-forbach-en-r1|title=Photos . La réserve de l'ASNL domine Forbach (3-1) dans le match au sommet de Régional 1|date=23 November 2019|website=www.estrepublicain.fr}}</ref> On 22 July 2022, he transferred to the Cypriot club [[Akritas Chlorakas]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vosgesmatin.fr/sport/2022/07/21/le-spinalien-wilguens-paugain-s-engage-en-premiere-division-chypriote|title=Football - Gazette des transferts. Le Spinalien Wilguens Paugain s'engage en première division chypriote|date=21 July 2022|website=www.vosgesmatin.fr}}</ref> In 2023, he moved to the Latvian club [[FK Auda]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sportpassioninfo.com/wilguens-paugain-a-la-porte-des-grenadiers/|title=Wilguens Paugain à la porte des Grenadiers - Sport Passion Info|date=23 November 2024|website=sportpassioninfo.com}}</ref> On 31 July 2024, he transferred to the Austrian club [[S.V. Zulte Waregem|Zulte Waregem]] until 2026.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.skn-stpoelten.at/skn-news/skn-st-polten-verpflichtet-wilguens-paugain|title=SKN St. Pölten verpflichtet Wilguens Paugain|website=www.skn-stpoelten.at}}</ref> On 1 February 2025, he joined [[S.V. Zulte Waregem|Zulte Waregem]] on loan for the second half of the 2024–25 season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.essevee.be/nieuws/wilguens-paugain-tweede-winteraankoop-voor-essevee|title=Wilguens Paugain tweede winteraankoop voor Essevee|website=Essevee Zulte Waregem|date=2 February 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in Haiti, Paugain moved to France at a young age and is a dual-citizen. He played for the [[France national under-18 football team|France U18]]s in friendlies in 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lepopulaire.fr/limoges-87100/football/vingt-bleuets-selectionnes_12965473/|title=Vingt Bleuets sélectionnés|date=31 August 2018}}</ref> In March 2025, he was called up to the [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]] for a set of friendlies.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tedactu.com/2025/03/05/emerson-laisse-convoque-pour-le-match-haiti-azerbaidjan/|title=Emerson Laissé convoqué pour le match Haïti-Azerbaïdjan|first=Marc Gorvens|last=Baptiste|date=6 March 2025}}</ref>

